<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 7:18PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Newberry and Saluda Counties through 745 PM EDT...
At 718 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Greenwood State Park, or 14 miles east of Greenwood, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Saluda, Hollywood Elementary School, Emory, Chappells, Chappells Fire
Station, Saluda Co Sheriff`s Office, Scurry Airport, Good Hope,
Hickory Grove, Wyses Ferry and Saluda High School.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
